## Academic Experience

```{=html}
<div class="cv-row">
  <div class="cv-date">2024.10–2025.12</div>
  <div class="cv-main">
    <a href="https://www.speechperceptionproductionlab.com/"
       target="_blank" rel="noopener"
       class="cv-inst">
      Speech Perception and Production Lab
    </a>, University of Chicago
  </div>
  <div class="cv-right">Research Assistant</div>
</div>

<div class="cv-body">
  <div></div>
  <div>
    <ul>
      <li>Contributed to postdoctoral research on the effects of exposure to non-native English vowel productions using eye-tracking paradigms.</li>
      <li>Gained mastery of the full research cycle, from experimental design and data collection to statistical analysis and result reporting.</li>
      <li>Used Praat to preprocess and analyze experimental data in WAV files, including spectrogram reading, acoustic boundary labeling, and data curation, etc.</li>
      <li>Attended weekly lab meetings to provide critical feedback and advice to team members on ongoing research projects.</li>
      <li>Collaborated with team members via Slack, Trello, and Box, ensuring transparent workflows and consistent data management.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="cv-subhead">Research Outcomes & Skills Gained:</div>
    <ul>
      <li>Developed expertise in acoustic analysis, linguistic experimental design, and team-based research workflows.</li>
      <li>Strengthened competence in statistical and computational methods (Python, R) applied to linguistic data analysis.</li>
      <li>Strengthened research writing skills and multimodal academic expression.</li>
      <li>Enhanced interdisciplinary collaboration and project communication skills.</li>
      <li>Lay a solid foundation for future research in language modeling, cognitive linguistics, and natural language processing at the master's level.</li>

    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Internship Experience

```{=html}
